- Inline message editing — v1.0.24. Replaced the prompt() with an in-place editor:
  clicking "edit" swaps the message body for a textarea (Enter saves, Shift+Enter
  newline, Esc cancels; empty/unchanged just cancels — delete still removes).
  renderMessages is the source of truth — a message whose id == editingMessageId
  draws the editor (seeded from editDraft) instead of body+reactions+actions — so
  an incoming message event re-rendering the whole list can't blow the editor away:
  the draft + caret + focus are captured before innerHTML reset and restored after
  (focus only re-grabbed if it was focused, so a background re-render never steals
  it). Switching channels abandons the edit; a save failure keeps the editor open
  so the draft isn't lost.
- Markdown links + inline images — v1.0.25. format.js now extracts links from each
  escaped run BEFORE the markdown pass (mirroring the emoji split): inlineMarkup
  does bold/italic/strike/mentions on the gaps only, so a URL is never fed through
  the italic rule — fixing the long-standing "underscores mangle URLs" bug. One
  LINK_RE matches, in priority order, [text](url) (https?:// only — [x](javascript:…)
  stays literal) or a bare http(s) URL; a bare URL whose path ends in an image
  extension (png/jpe?g/gif/webp/avif/bmp/svg, optional ?query/#frag) renders inline
  as <a class=msg-image-link><img class=msg-image …></a> instead of its text. The
  escape-first invariant is intact: URLs go into href/src already escaped, so a quote
  can't break the attribute (unit-tested). New formatMessage opts {embedImages} —
  search rows pass embedImages:false (an embedded image would fight the whole-row
  click-to-jump; they fall back to plain links). Composer bonus: pasting a single
  URL onto a non-empty selection wraps it as [selection](url).
- Presence flicker fix — v1.0.26. presence.update is now debounced ~1s per user in
  the client: schedulePresenceUpdate holds an incoming change, a newer one for the
  same user replaces it, and if the latest value already matches what's displayed
  the pending change is dropped without repainting — so a brief connectivity blip
  (offline→online flip) never paints a flickered dot, while a sustained change
  still applies after a second. Our own user is exempt (status is server→broadcast
  with no optimistic local update, so debouncing self would lag a deliberate pick).
  Pending flips are flushed on reconnect (resync re-pulls the authoritative roster).
  The equality test is a pure state.js helper, presenceMatches (unit-tested).
- THE PIECE DE RESISTANCE — Claude agent wired into the chat — v1.0.32–34. Works
  a treat. A bot user authenticates with a bearer token (random+SHA-256-hashed,
  same scheme as sessions) minted at POST /api/admin/bot-tokens (admin-only;
  v1.0.33 added a management UI, v1.0.34 a user picker + project-scoped
  permissions). scripts/claude-bridge (bash, deps: curl/jq/claude — no Go change
  beyond the token API) polls a private #claude channel it's a member of, forwards
  each new human message to `claude --print` running in the repo dir, and posts the
  result back by editing an "⚙️ Working…" placeholder in place (falls back to a new
  post if the edit fails). Cursor (last-seen id) persists to a state file and
  advances BEFORE running Claude so a crash never replays a request; output is
  trimmed to stay under the 4096-byte message limit. So work requests — commits,
  deploys, the lot — can now be sent from inside Rivendell itself.
- Voice calling, phases 1+2 — v1.1.0. P2P WebRTC signaled over the existing WS hub;
  no media server, no new Go deps (design in docs/voice.md). Phase 1 (signaling
  skeleton): config vars (RIVENDELL_STUN_URL / TURN_URL / TURN_SECRET), hub voice
  state map + point-to-point routing for voice.* WS types (offer/answer/ice relayed
  verbatim after a channel-access check; join/leave/mute fan out an authoritative
  voice.state), GET /api/channels/{id}/voice, GET /api/rtc/credentials (HMAC
  time-limited TURN creds, no coturn user DB), and the 30 s DM ring-timeout
  goroutine. Phase 2 (DM calling): voice.js with getUserMedia + one
  RTCPeerConnection (offer/answer/ICE-trickle), DM call UI (📞 button, incoming-call
  ring banner with accept/decline + soft Web Audio ring, active-call strip), and
  mute/deafen (local audio gate; mute still broadcast for the indicator). End-to-end
  green: two users in a DM can call each other. STUN-only works on a LAN / real-IP
  network; TURN (coturn) is the relay fallback for symmetric NAT / CGNAT — see the
  backlog + ops notes for standing it up.

